RT @Ripushko: Today is the 31st anniversary of "the Little Mermaid"!
In this connection, I share a piece of my closed comic in this thread)â€¦
It may be later this week. It may be later this month. It may be Spring. It may be Summer. But I want a clear date for #TheLittleMermaid to start shooting....
What I want from the live-action cast and crew of #TheLittleMermaid is transparency - a clear start date for filming and indications that everyone will try to stick to it...

I'm sick of this happening all the time to both the #Universal and #Disney versions. #TheLittleMermaid is one of my favourite stories of all time - I love BOTH the very different Andersen and Disney visions. I don't want to feel like any big adaptations of it are cursed...

My anxieties over the delays to #Disney's live-action #TheLittleMermaid have been fueled by the several failed attempts to make a sadder Andersen-style version. I remember all the times Sofia Coppola and @ChloeGMoretz hyped their versions, only for them to pull the plug...
RT @FairyTaleFanboy: I love the #Disney original with all my heart, but it has plenty of flaws (esp. at the climax) so I want to see how thâ€¦

I love the #Disney original with all my heart, but it has plenty of flaws (esp. at the climax) so I want to see how the live-action version of #TheLittleMermaid improves things. I also want to see how it uses live-action to surpass the limits of the 2007 stage adaptation...

I want to see this movie. I want to see Halle Bailey of @chloexhalle kill it as one of the most interesting #Disney leads of all time. I want to see the  supporting cast reinterpreting the other characters. I want to see both the old songs and new additions to #TheLittleMermaid..

What DOES worry and frustrate me is the fact that #TheLittleMermaid has postponed the start of shooting FOUR TIMES since it was forced to abandon its plans to start rolling the camera in Spring 2020. All other #COVID19 disrupted shoots have begun, resumed or concluded by now...

IMO, #TheLittleMermaid is probably easier to shoot in socially distanced format than the delayed live-action shoots, esp. with the Ariel's fishy friends having pre-recorded their lines already. But I can understand why #Disney would want to be cautious for the next few weeks...

If the team behind the live-action #TheLittleMermaid can pull off a socially distanced shoot during #Lockdown, that's fine by me. If they choose to delay further like #Willow and #DoctorStrange 2, that's fine by me. What ISN'T fine is the continued wait for more information...
